ca.uhn.fhir.rest.annotation

Annotation Type Search


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
@Target(value=METHOD)
public @interface Search
    RESTful method annotation used for a method which provides the FHIR "search" method.
    See Also:
    the FHIR Search definition

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      String queryName
      If specified, this the name for the Named Query
      Class<? extends IResource> type
      The return type for this method.

    • Element Detail

      • queryName

        public abstract String queryName
        If specified, this the name for the Named Query

        See the FHIR specification section on named queries

        Default:
        ""

      • type

        public abstract Class<? extends IResource> type
        The return type for this method. This generally does not need to be populated for resource providers in a server implementation, but often does need to be populated in client implementations using IBasicClient or IRestfulClient, or in plain providers on a server.

        This value also does not need to be populated if the return type for a method annotated with this annotation is sufficient to determine the type of resource provided. E.g. if the method returns Patient or List<Patient>, the server/client will automatically determine that the Patient resource is the return type, and this value may be left blank.

        Default:
        ca.uhn.fhir.model.api.IResource.class
